==English==

===Noun===
'''[[big]] [[deal]]'''
#{{idiom}} Something very [[important]], [[difficult]], or of [[concern]].
#:''It's a '''big deal''' to him to get this promotion.''
#:''It's no '''big deal''' if you don't finish.''

===Interjection===
#{{idiom}} (ironically) Indicates that something is not important or impressive; [[so what]].
#:''He can run a mile in 15 minutes?  '''Big deal!''' Some people can do it in four.''